import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    group_sizes = data.groupby('group').size()
    sns.histplot(group_sizes, kde=False, bins=3)
    plt.xlabel('Group ID')
    plt.ylabel('Group Size')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    group_sizes = data.groupby('group').size().reset_index(name='count')
    ax = sns.barplot(x='group', y='count', data=group_sizes)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the most common group size?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    person_group_counts = data.groupby('person')['group'].count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='person', y='group', data=person_group_counts)
    plt.title('Which person is in the most groups?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    group_counts = data.groupby('person')['group'].count()
    sns.histplot(group_counts, kde=False, bins=range(1, group_counts.max() + 1))
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of group membership across people?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from matplotlib_venn import venn3
from collections import defaultdict

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    group_sets = defaultdict(set)
    for _, row in data.iterrows():
        group_sets[row['group']].add(row['person'])
    
    venn3([group_sets[1], group_sets[2], group_sets[3]], set_labels=('Group 1', 'Group 2', 'Group 3'))
    
    plt.title('What is the overlap between groups?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
